From f7525811e4cab468696ae2cffd3fd7838f10e233 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fabiano Correa Mercer <fabiano.correamercer@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 09:29:49 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add SRC IP for default routes

For interfaces configured with a gateway parameter:

- The interface ADDRESS is used as the source IP (SRC)
when creating routes.
- This behavior is primarily intended for default routes.

IPv6 route creation may fail if the interface ADDRESS is
still in a tentative state due to Duplicate Address Detection.

If the IP address is in DAD FAILED or remains TENTATIVE:
- The route is created without the SRC parameter to ensure the
default route is still installed and connectivity to the
system is preserved.

Signed-off-by: Fabiano Correa Mercer <fabiano.correamercer@windriver.com>
